column1: VS3 MORTALITY BY CAUSE* - 2007 REGISTRATIONS TO 2007 BOUNDARIES

column3: III Diseases of the blood and
VIII Diseases of the ear and
XII Diseases of the skin and

column2: The figures for individual cause categories exclude deaths aged under 28 days.
*Cause of death as given in the death register and based on the doctor's or coroner's certificate of
cause of death; this is known as 'original' cause of death.
Previously VS3 was based on 'final' cause of death which takes account of any additional
information provided by medical practitioners or coroners after the death has been registered.
See Report: Death registrations in England and Wales 2004: causes in Health Statistics Quarterly
For 2006 registrations accelerated registrations (inquest verdict 'pending') were coded to Y33.9for 2007 registrations these deaths are now coded to U50.9.
